— Attributed to no one in particular... but we all know someone who'd claim it
"Greed is the finest trait of humanity — they’ll claw through filth for a scrap of gold, then die clutching it, as if Hell accepts bribes."
Her touch is rot. Her breath is ruin. She devours the souls of the desperate, yet they still serve.
She didn’t create life—she twisted it. Her children were made not of love but of greed, stitched together from decay and bound to her by obedience.
Before rot consumed the underworld, the All-Mother was born from filth, a bloated mass of flesh, bone, and hunger.
